      <div rendition="class:83225 maturity:83211" type="edition" xml:lang="san-Latn">
        <!--
Encoded for Siddham by Eszter Somogyi, following Ramesh and Tewari's edition unless otherwise noted in comments. Version of January 2019. Comments below by Dániel Balogh are offered "as is" and do not represent a thoroughly researched or considered opinion.
-->
        <!--
RT's note about the plate: The plate is broken vertically into two halves.
-->
        <p><lb n="1"/>svasti<supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied>
valkhā<supplied reason="omitted">ḥ</supplied> paramabhaṭṭāraka-pādānuddhyāto mahārāja-bhaṭṭārakaḥ kuśalī</p>
        <p><lb n="2"/>gādhinagara-pathake riṭikāgrāharake samupagatā<unclear>n</unclear> sv<choice>
            <sic>a</sic>
            <corr>ā</corr>
          </choice>n āyuktakā<unclear>n</unclear>
<lb n="3"/>grāma-prativāsinaś ca bodhayati
</p>
        <p>viditavyo <supplied reason="subaudible">’</supplied>stu yathaiṣa grāmo<!--
L3. DB: RT's reading viditavyo is probably correct, but the intent must have been viditam vo.
--><lb n="4"/>mayā val<sic>gu</sic>-cāturvvaidya-samūhasya Ācandrārka-samakālīna-
<lb n="5"/>putra-pautrānvaya-bhojya Agrāhāro nisr̥ṣṭaḥ<supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied> tad yuṣmābhir asy<choice>
            <sic>a</sic>
            <corr>o</corr>
          </choice><lb break="no" n="6"/>
citā<supplied reason="omitted">ḥ</supplied> pratyayāḥ Upaneyā Ājñā-vidheyaiś ca bhavitavya<supplied reason="omitted">M</supplied><!--
L6. DB: RT print pratyayaḥ; the plate has °yāḥ. I retain RT's emendation °citāḥ but the intent may have been °cita-pratyayāḥ.
--></p>
        <p><lb n="7"/>svamukhājñā likhita<choice>
            <sic>n</sic>
            <corr>m</corr>
          </choice> mayā r<choice>
            <sic>a</sic>
            <corr>ā</corr>
          </choice>jyādhikr̥ta-kr̥ṣṇena</p>
        <p>savva <num value="129"><g type="numeral">100</g><g type="numeral">20</g> 9</num>
<lb n="8"/>katti śu <num value="7">7</num><!--
L8 RT emend katti to kārttika.
--></p>
        <ab><lb n="01"/>bhaṭṭārakasya śāsana<choice>
            <sic>ḥ</sic>
            <corr>ṁ</corr>
          </choice><!--
L margin.1 is engraved on the left margin, bottom to top, characters rotated 90° counterclockwise.
--></ab>
